<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Inks Postal Agreement with Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 19 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Post Office inked a
letter of understanding here today with the visiting Afghan
Transport Delegation for joining the rehabilitation efforts in
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, Pakistan will immediately restore
mail links with Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will supply postal equipment of essential nature
required for the resurrection of postal network in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani experts and consultants will carry out spot surveys
and studies to assess the extent of damage to Afghan postal
network to determine the magnitude of technical assistance needed.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan will ascertain Afghan post's training requirements to
design courses tailored to their needs.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion, I.U. Khan, director general of
Pakistan Post Office, expressed the hope the new agreement will
herald a new era of collaboration in the postal sector of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He also assured the Afghan delegates every assistance and help
his administration could provide in restoring the normal postal
services functions.
</P>
<P>
Sayaf Mustafa from the Ministry of Communications of
Afghanistan, hoped that mail links between the two countries will
reinforce the traditional bonds which have always existed between
the peoples of the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
