<HEADLINE> EC Sues Belgium, Ireland for Water Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
has decided to take Belgium and Ireland to court on charge of
discharging dangerous substances into the aquatic environment, it
was reported today.
</P>
<P>
The EC will bring the case to the European Court of Justice
against the failure of the two countries to respect a certain
directive of the European Union on pollution, which contains an
important set of safeguards against water pollution.
</P>
<P>
So far, Belgium has no reaction to the accusation made
by the EC, which therefore decided that an application to the
court was necessary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
