<HEADLINE> EU Enjoys Trade Surplus for Nine Consecutive Quarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, December 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Union's trade
surplus with the rest of the world reached 11 billion ECUs (about
14 billion U.S. dollars) in the first half of this year, EU's
statistical office (Eurostat) said today.
</P>
<P>
The surplus was 1.5 billion ECUs (some two billion dollars) in
the first quarter and 9.5 billion ECUs (some 12 billion dollars)
in the second quarter.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, the positive trade balance has been going on for
nine consecutive quarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
