<HEADLINE> Shanghai Team Wins Chinese Table Tennis Club Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DONGGUAN, Guangzhou Province, December 19 (Xinhua) -- Teenager
Wang Liqin upset world champion Kong Linghui 2-0 to lead Shanghai
for the men's team title at the Chinese Table Tennis Club
Championship here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Wang defeated Kong 26-24, 21-14 in Shanghai's
3-1 final victory over Heilongjiang while Jiangsu clinched the
women's team title with a 3-0 sweep over Henan, which was led by
world and Olympic champion Deng Yaping.
</P>
<P>
Li Ju rallied from a first down to oust Deng Yaping 18-21,
23-21, 21-11 in the opening set. Yang Ying beat Zhang Hui 2-1 and
Wu Na rounded off the score to 3-0 with a 2-0 win over Li Qiumei.
</P>
<P>
The individuals competitions are scheduled on Friday and
Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
