<HEADLINE> World Bank Grants Loan to Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today
announced the approval of a 28.5 million U.S. dollar loan to
Indonesia to help finance a 45.3 million Intensified Iodine
Deficiency Control Project.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to reduce the prevalence of iodine deficiency
and will boost the country's iodine deficiency control program by
developing policies to increase competitiveness of the salt
industry and by increasing the supply, quality and consumption of
iodized salt in the country.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the World Bank loan, the remaining 16.8 million
dollars will be financed by the Government of Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
