<HEADLINE> 1.5 Million People Visits Zimbabwe This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 19 (Xinhua) -- President Robert Mugabe said
here today that a total of 1.5 million people are expected to
have visited Zimbabwe this year, earning the country 200 million
U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
In his state of the nation address to parliament, Mugabe said
in 1995, Zimbabwe had 1.4 million visitors and total earnings of
130 million U.S. Dollars from the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
He said tourism had since independence in 1980 grown at annual
average of 10 percent in terms of visitor arrivals and 29 percent
in total earnings.
</P>
<P>
''The tourism industry is increasingly becoming important to
the economy in terms of the creation and distribution of
wealth,'' Mugabe said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
