<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nordic Countries Sign Schengen Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 19 (Xinhua)-- Sweden and the other Nordic
countries signed today in Luxembourg an agreement on a passport
union in accordance with the Schengen Convention.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is to be ratified by the countries concerned.
The Swedish government will prepare a memorandum which will be
circulated to various bodies for comments during the spring and
the Parliament will make a decision in the autumn of 1997.
</P>
<P>
There will be increased freedom of movement after signing the
Schengen Agreement. At the same time, the Nordic countries will be
able to retain their passport union.
</P>
<P>
There are critics of Schengen membership, however, who fear
that it will lead to more restrictive asylum policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
