<HEADLINE> China Provides Agricultural Aid to Namibia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 19 (Xinhua) -- China agreed to provide
Namibia with 15 million U.S. Dollars for funding several
agricultural projects in the southern African country, according
to Chinese diplomats in Windhoek, capital of Namibia.
</P>
<P>
An agreement between the two governments was signed in
Windhoek on Wednesday by Chinese Ambassador to Namibia, Lian
Zhengbao, and Namibian Finance Minister, Nangolo Mbumba.
</P>
<P>
The aid will be used to develop irrigation projects along the
Orange River bordering South Africa, among other agricultural
projects in northern Namibia.
</P>
<P>
China has so far provided about 50 million U.S. Dollars for
agricultural development projects in Namibia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
