<HEADLINE> Angola's National Unity Govt to Be Formed in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
January
</P>
<P>
LUANDA, December 19 (Xinhua) -- A government of national
unity and reconciliation will be set up in January and UNITA's
MPs will arrive in Luanda in the same month, President Eduardo
Dos Santos said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Council of Republic, Dos Santos also said
his government will start implementing the political tasks of
achieving national reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
Referring to UNITA'S announcement on December 11 that it
had ended the assembly of soldiers and the handing over of all
its weapons, Santos said, "it is a major step in the process of
carrying out the peace agreement."
</P>
<P>
The peace accord signed in Zambia in 1994 provides that the
National Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA)
should send its soldiers to the assembly points and hand over
all its weapons by 1996.
</P>
<P>
What we should do now is to end the formation of a unified
army, start administration throughout the territory, control
the border lines and remove all obstacles that block the free
movement of personnel, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
