<HEADLINE> Zairean President to Nominate Crisis Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 19 (Xinhua) -- Zairean President Sese Seko
Mobutu will nominate a crisis government within 48 hours to deal
with the Tutsi insurgency in the eastern Kivu region, the Agence
France Presse (AFP) quoted Zairean officials as saying today.
</P>
<P>
Mobutu nominated Wednesday a new chief of the Zairean army,
General Mahel Bokoungo Lieko, after sacking last month General
Eluki Monga Aunda for failing to stop the advance of the Tutsi
Banyamulenge rebels, on a revolt since October.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of Zaire's opposition parties and government officials
held a meeting in Kinshasa today to discuss the establishment of a
crisis government, to be consisted of "people suitable for joining
a crisis government," AFP quoted those attending the meeting as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The government of Prime Minister Leon Kengo Wa Dondo has
submitted a list of names for the crisis government to President
Mobutu, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The main opposition leader Etienne Tshisekedi said that he
would not join the crisis government, expected to be headed by the
incumbent prime minister himself.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman of the presidential party Kitenge Yezu said that
Zaire needs a "strong, credible and above all representative
government whose only concern is to wash the shame which is the
occupation by the enemy armies of a part of the national
territory."
</P>
<P>
Zaire has accused Rwanda and Uganda of invading the eastern and
northeastern parts of the country to support the Banyamulenge
rebels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
