<HEADLINE> Independent Organ Set Up to Investigate Jewish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 19 (Xinhua) -- An independent commission of
nine experts has been formally established to investigate Jewish
property in Swiss banks during World War Two, the Swiss government
announced today in Bern.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss government has allocated 5 million francs (about 4
million U.S. dollars) to the commission and insisted that the
commission, empowered to lift bank secrecy, is totally independent
and authoritative.
</P>
<P>
From January 1997, the commission will start the investigation,
which may take three to five years.
</P>
<P>
The commission is led by Jean-Francois Bergier, a Swiss
professor of history. Four foreign experts in the commission are
former Polish Foreign Minister Wladyslaw Bartoszewski, American
historian at the Museum of the Holocaust in Washington D.C. Ms
Sybil Milton, Israeli historian Saul Friedlaender and American
professor of history at the University of Princeton Harold James.
</P>
</TEXT>
