<HEADLINE> Ministerial Meeting of Lake Victoria Fisheries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 19 (Xinhua) -- The first session of the
Council of Ministers of the Lake Victoria Fisheries Organization
opened here today, with a call on member states to ensure the
sustainable use of Lake Victoria resources.
</P>
<P>
The call was made by Ugandan Vice- President and Minister of
Agriculture, Animal Industry and Fisheries Specioza Wandira
Kazibwe while opening the meeting.
</P>
<P>
She said that the environment of the lake is continuously
changing, and hence the need for cooperation among the regional
stake-holders.
</P>
<P>
She urged the organization's member states to increase the
harvesting of the lake resources by improving the livelihood of
fish and the research and training on the sustainable use of the
lake resources.
</P>
<P>
Kazibwe said there is need to promote fish farming and
creation of a bank on the fauna and flora of the lake to ensure
the sustainability of species.
</P>
<P>
She challenged the stake-holders to develop the transport
system on the lake, as a major action to improve in the movement
of people, goods and services.
</P>
<P>
The session is being attended by delegations from Kenya,
Tanzania and Uganda. 
</P>
