<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Stresses Importance of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 19 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni today stressed the importance of education, saying
education is a precondition for national development, Radio
Uganda reported.
</P>
<P>
The president said education is a precondition for natioanl
development since it is the fundamental basis for the development
of human resources.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a workshop on free primary education for four
children per family held at Makerere University here, Museveni
said that his government's concept of education is based on the
principle of education for all.
</P>
<P>
The two-day workshop, organized by the Ministry of Education,
is being attended by local officials for education and leaders of
non-governmental organizations involved in the education sector.
</P>
<P>
Museveni explained that the progra of modernizing Uganda will
be achieved through industrialization, agricultural modernization
and education for all.
</P>
<P>
He said that in order to transform the economy, the human
being must also be transformed to become a skilled worker, and
this can best be done through education.
</P>
<P>
The provision of education for all will be attained step by
step in a systematic manner,he added. He urged the people of
Uganda to work together to implement the program and be patient
so that this first step is achieved before the government takes
on larger tasks.
</P>
<P>
He cautioned, however, that by starting with four children,
the government is sending a clear signal to parents to share
responsibility for educating their children and not abandon it
entirely to the government.
</P>
<P>
Uganda will start the free education program for four children
of each family on January next year. 
</P>
