<HEADLINE> UK to Send Experts to Help Resolve Hostage Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 19 (Xinhua) -- The British government
announced here today that it would send a group of experienced
experts to Peru to help release some four hundred hostages from
the Japanese embassy compound in Lima, Peru.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Xinhua this afternoon, a British
Foreign Office spokesman said that the British government is to
send "a team of experts with a range of skills to strengthen the
British ambassador's team in Lima."
</P>
<P>
"They are being sent to advise the ambassador and liaison as
necessary with the Peruvian authorities" in an effort to help
resolve the hostage crisis, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Britain's ambassador to Lima had attended
the reception at the Japanese embassy but left before local
guerillas started the attack and held those hostages on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
