<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Hails CIS Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin said that the Commonwealth of Independents States (CIS)
has successfully developed in the direction of European-Asian
integration since it was founded in Alma Ata five years ago,
reported Kazakhstan Telegraph Agency today.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin made the remarks in a telegraph sent to Kazakh
President Nursultan Nazarbayev on the eve of the fifth anniversary
of the CIS, which falls on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The CIS states have established a cooperation mechanism based
on mutual benefit, equality and mutual respect of sovereignty,
said the Russian president.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin expressed the belief that the CIS will become an
important element promoting world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
He also thanked Nazarbayev for his contribution in advancing
cooperation among the CIS states.
</P>
<P>
The CIS, which was founded after the disintegration of the
former Soviet Union, groups 12 out of the 15 former Soviet
republics except Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
