<HEADLINE> ADB Provides Aid for Mongolia's Banking Reorganization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) decided on Thursday to grant Mongolia 35 million
U.S. dollars in preferential loans and 3 million dollars in
technology aid as part of its support to the country's
reorganization of its banking system.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian government decided last week to close two
loss-making banks -- the People's Bank and the Insurance Bank --
in a bid to protect the country's economy and the interests of the
depositors, according to the government press office.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank and the Insurance Bank, the biggest and 4th
biggest commercial bank in Mongolia, respectively suffered a 17.4
billion-tugrik deficit (about 250 million dollars) and a 5.9
billion-tugrik one (about 85 million dollars) due to poor
management.
</P>
<P>
The government has set up two banks -- the Rejuvenation Bank
and Deposit Bank -- to take over the closed ones.
</P>
<P>
The depositors reacted calmly to the reorganization thanks to
the government's measure to ensure their interests.
</P>
</TEXT>
