<HEADLINE> Shanghai's First Joint Power Venture Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 20 (Xinhua) -- US-based General Electric and
the Electric Power Company of Shanghai signed an agreement today
to establish the first jointly-owned electricity company in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The new company will involve a total investment of 2.045 billion
yuan (250 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, 30 percent of the funding is capital from
the two companies. The remainder will come from loans to be
extended by ten commercial banks in Britain, France, Germany and
Japan.
</P>
<P>
The company will mainly operate the Zhadian Combustion Turbine
Project. Four generating units of the project are nearly complete
and are expected to greatly relieve the pressure on the city's
power supply. 
</P>
