<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's First Black Bear Nursery Built in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The first black bear nursery
in the country has been set up in the city of Fanyu, and is now
home to eight of the State-protected creatures.
</P>
<P>
The nursery, located in south China's Guangdong Province,
covers nearly 10,000 square meters and houses eight Selenarctos
Thibetanuses, a kind of black bear under second-grade State
protection.
</P>
<P>
The bears were rescued from a bear bile producer in Huizhou,
where they were caged and treated harshly. The bears recovered
quickly, thanks to efforts of both Chinese and British
veterinarians.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong-based International Fund for Animal Welfare
invested a total of two million yuan to build the nursery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
