<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Iranian authorities today
blamed Saudi opposition group known as Salafis for bombing the
U.S. military bases, which killed 19 American soldiers in
Dhahran last June.
</P>
<P>
Iran's leading hardline clergyman Ayatollah Ahmad Jannati said
that he gave a 99 percent probability that the explosion was
carried out by Salafis.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that Salafis is
the opposition group that strongly opposes Saudi Arabian rule on
the bases of ideological differences and it can not stand any
more the presence of the U.S. troops in the kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Addressing large number of Friday prayer worshippers at Tehran
University campus, Jannati said that "Dhahran explosion was an
internal issue in Saudi Arabia."
</P>
<P>
"Riyadh had found no document yet to support Iran's
involvement in the case," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Ayatollah cautioned the United States not to take any
"insanely course" against Iran regarding the blast.
</P>
<P>
The Friday prayer leader further pointed out that Saudi
Arabian officials are fully aware of the fact, adding that the
United States, which has some ulterior motives, wants to somehow
implicate Iran in the Dhahran bombing.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the United States is ignorant of this fact that
by threatening the Islamic Republic of Iran, it would bear no
other results than further infuriating the Iranian nation and
heightening their hatred against the U.S.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
