<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Re-employment Service Center Set up in Coastal Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Dalian Re-employment
Service Center, which trains displaced workers at no cost to the
individuals, opened in this coastal city in northeastern Liaoning
Province today.
</P>
<P>
According to its news briefing, the move is part of
the Dalian City government's effort to speed up enterprise reform
and relieve local state firms of their large numbers of displaced
workers.
</P>
<P>
The center aims to help the workers find new jobs within two
years. However, anyone who twice declines the work opportunities
offered by the center will be listed as jobless.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises that want their displaced workers to participate in
the training must pay 6,500 yuan per person signed up. The city
government will also provide 3,500 yuan for each trainee.
</P>
<P>
The age limit for men who want to participate in the program is
45, and for women, 40.
</P>
<P>
Once in the program, the trainees will still be regarded as
employees of their original units, and the center will pay their
wages, which will be 80 percent of the lowest amount set by the
city government, but still higher than the official bottom line of
daily income for local residents.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, state enterprises in Dalian have
dismissed over 30,000 workers, while 50,000 people have found new
positions through the city's reemployment program.
</P>
<P>
Dalian plans to lay off 100,000 employees in these state firms
in a bid to further ease their burden, according to the briefing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
