<HEADLINE> Technical Upgrading Vital to Existing Enterprises: Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
today that large-scale projects to upgrade and advance technology
serve as important steps to ensure the fundamental shift in the
the structure and growth mode of the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
The premier made the comment during the opening ceremony for
the transformation project of the No.1 Thermal Power Plant
affiliated with the Beijing Thermal Power Plant, which supplies
heat and electricity for the central government organizations,
foreign embassies and the eastern part of the city.
</P>
<P>
The No.1 Power Plant was listed as one of the country's 156 key
projects during the First Five-Year Plan period (1953-1957).
</P>
<P>
With the rapid economic development in the city, the demand for
heat and electricity has sharply increased, while requirements for
safe production have become more strict.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, who formerly worked in the country's power industry,
said that it is time to upgrade the thermal power plant, as most
of the equipment there is too old to handle extended use.
</P>
<P>
He said that the finished project will greatly reduce local air
pollution, and guarantee steady and reliable electricity and heat
supplies for the capital city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
