<HEADLINE> China Northwest Orders 10 A320 Jetliner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- China Aviation Supplies Corp.,
China Northwest Airlines, and Airbus Industrie today signed a
contract to order 10 A320 passenger jets from the European
consortium.
</P>
<P>
The 10 twin-engine A320 jetliners, worth over 300 million US
dollars, will be delivered to China Northwest before 2000. The
aircraft will have an eight-seat first-class section and 150
economy seats.
</P>
