airliners to be purchased by China before the end of the
century. The 1.5 billion US dollar deal was struck during Chinese
Premier Li Peng's official visit to France last April.
</P>
<P>
China Northwest Airlines, based in the well-known tourist city
of Xi'an, Shaanxi Province, is one of the six major carriers in
the country. Its fleet consists mainly of Russian-made aircraft
and the Airbus family. 
