<HEADLINE> China Association for Promoting Democracy Meeting in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The fifth plenary session of
the Ninth Central Committee of the China Association for Promoting
Democracy ended today in Beijing, pledging that the organization
will better fulfill its assigned duties.
</P>
<P>
The meeting vowed that the association will do more to
participate in political and government affairs, maintain
political stability and unity, and contribute more to China's
revitalization and reunification in the new year.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, Lei Jieqiong, chairwoman of the
association, said 1997 is an important year in Chinese history,
when the country will resume the exercise of sovereignty over Hong
Kong, the Communist Party of China (CPC) will hold its 15th
National Congress, and her association will hold its Eighth
National Conference.
</P>
<P>
She required all the members of her organization to carry out
the spirit of the sixth plenum of the 14th CPC Central Committee,
and strive to improve their work.
</P>
<P>
Chen Shunli, executive vice-chairman of the association's
Central Committee, delivered a work report to make arrangements
for the duties in 1997.
</P>
<P>
It was also decided at the four-day meeting that the Eighth
National Conference of the China Association for Promoting
Democracy will be held during the fourth quarter of next year.
</P>
<P>
The association is one of the eight leading non-communist
parties in China. It has a total of 62,000 members, mainly middle
and high level intellectuals from the education, culture, and
science circles.  
