<HEADLINE> Shaoshan Mao Zedong Library Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Shaoshan Mao Zedong Library
opened today in the city of Shaoshan, in Hunan Province -- the
hometown of the late Chinese Leader.
</P>
<P>
The library, named by Chinese President Jiang Zemin, is located
near Mao's native village of Shaoshanchong.
</P>
<P>
Standing next to the Mao Zedong Memorial Hall and the Mao
Zedong Bronze Statue, the library covers 5,000 sq m and has a
collection of 500,000 books.
</P>
<P>
There are presently more than 110,000 books and periodicals on
the shelves, mainly publications that were read by Mao and still
bear his margin notes. There are also copies of Mao's writings and
15,000 volumes of his works in 1,500 versions and 25 languages.
</P>
<P>
The collection also features academic papers and works on the
late leader, written by Chinese and foreign scholars. 
</P>
