<HEADLINE> Sichuan Hosts Int'l Seminar on Financing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 20 (Xinhua) -- An international seminar on
financing opened today in Chengdu, the capital of southwest
China's Sichuan Province, which was attended by over 200 financial
experts from home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The participants shared their experience on international
financing activities, including loans, issuing shares and bonds,
setting up funds and financing for certain projects.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Chinese enterprises in need of funds mainly rely on
bank loans and issuing shares, while other choices are limited,
according to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan, a large inland province, now has 6,238 foreign-funded
firms, using a total foreign capital of 10.9 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Due to a shortage of funds, Sichuan needs to introduce 1.5
billion US dollar foreign investment annually, but so far this
year has actually utilized one billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Presently, only one local company issues H shares, the shares
of Chinese enterprises that are listed in Hong Kong. 
</P>
