<HEADLINE> Australian Wine Makers to Face Grapes Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Wine makers in Australia
would have to make wine with marginally less wine grape production
over the next three years, said a report issued by the Australian
Bureau of Agricultural and Resource Economics.
</P>
<P>
The report, on wine grape production and intake up to 1998-99,
combined estimates for the 1995-96 harvest with projections of
production for the next three years.
</P>
<P>
"Between 1996-97 and 1998-99 wine makers plan to increase their
intake of wine grapes by about 181,000 tons," it said. "Although
production is expected to increase over this period, there will be
a projected 27,000- ton shortfall relative to the planned intake
in 1998-99."  
</P>
