<HEADLINE> Recordable Laser Compact Discs under Production in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- A high-tech company in
Shenzhen City, a special economic zone in south China's Guangdong
Province, has set up China's first production line for recordable
laser compact discs.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Xianke Digital Laser Disc Company has invested 5.1
million US dollars to produce the new kind of information storage
medium.
</P>
<P>
People can only usually retrieve information from CDs used in
computers and video recorders, but can not store data on them.
</P>
<P>
The new type of blank CD can be used to contain personal data
and household recordings, as well as information in aerospace
industry.
</P>
<P>
Recordable CDs are in great demand on world markets, according
to Wang Shijie, general manager of the company. His company, he
added, is able to produce 1.5 million such discs a year, 70
percent of them for export.
</P>
<P>
In this way, the company is able to rake in a net profit of two
million US dollars a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
