<HEADLINE> Trading Plummets at Shanghai Bourse This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange
Composite Index closed at 885.24 points today, down 20.25 percent
over last Friday, while the SSE 30 Index declined by 13.14 percent
to close at 2,405.74 points.
</P>
<P>
A total of 27.469 billion yuan changed hands this week, 58.15
percent less than last week.
</P>
<P>
Tradings and share prices plunged heavily on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange (SSE) in the first trading days after the authorities put
limits on fluctuations of prices, and the People's Daily warned
against the overheated market.
</P>
<P>
In the later half of the week, however, trading and prices
managed to avoid further plunges and became stablized, while the
trading volume also recovered moderately.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, some blue chips, with Sichuan Changhong as
the leader, still saw a stable movement and active trading this
week.
</P>
<P>
Local investors have showed their understanding of the
authorities' new measures to limit the ups and downs.
</P>
<P>
Professor Gu gongyun from the Shanghai-based East China
Politics and Law University said that the moves conform with the
international practice, and are of great significance to
reducing market risks and protecting the interests of the mass of
smaller investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
