<HEADLINE> New Library Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's new showpiece
library, China's second largest, and one of the ten largest
libraries in the world, opened today.
</P>
<P>
Local officials, including Shanghai Municipal Party Secretary
Huang Ju and city mayor Xu Kuangdi, attended the opening ceremony
this morning.
</P>
<P>
With a total floor space of 83,000 square meters, the library
boasts 10 million books, 30 million patent documents and a
computerized system.
</P>
<P>
It has a stack room which can house 13 million volumes, and 24
reading rooms where domestic and overseas publications, electronic
and audio-video publications, and more than 3,000 seats are
available.
</P>
<P>
Exhibition halls, meeting rooms, multi-function halls and
research institutes will make the library a center of study,
academic exchanges and research.
</P>
<P>
A major cultural project costing 620 million yuan (74.7 million
US dollars), the new library is considered to be a symbol of the
progressive city, said Ma Yuanliang, curator of the library.
</P>
<P>
The library's computer network has been linked with major
domestic and international networks, such as the Internet,
allowing readers access to the latest information on the
information super highway.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the library will become famous for its 1.7 million
valuable ancient books, and the largest amount of rubbings and
family trees in the country.
</P>
<P>
"We've designated several showrooms and reading rooms to
display our unique collections," said deputy curator Chen Xiejun.
</P>
<P>
Currently Shanghai has 557 libraries for its 13 million people.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's National Library is the largest library in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
