<HEADLINE> Chinese Economic Zone And Hong Kong Indispensable to Each Other </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The special economic zone of
Shenzhen, in south China's Guangdong Province, serves as China's
most important link with the world economy and has become the
largest market for Hong Kong capital.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen is the only Chinese mainland city bordering Hong Kong,
and by the end of September, Hong Kong investment there totalled
more than 7 billion US dollars, accounting for 65 percent of the
total overseas investment in the special economic zone, which was
China's first. A survey has shown that a third of Hong Kong's
currency is circulating in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Seventy Percent of Shenzhen's industrial output value is
produced by foreign-funded companies, 80 percent of which are from
Hong Kong, whereas 70 percent of the fresh milk, 40 percent of the
live chickens, and 25 percent of the fresh vegetables on the Hong
Kong market come from Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen imported 1.67 billion US dollars worth of Hong Kong
products last year, while its 38.77 billion US dollars worth of
exports helped push Hong Kong to eighth place on the world's trade
list.
</P>
<P>
There were 56.71 million people going in and out of Shenzhen
port last year, or 50 percent of China's total number of
travelers, contributing a large part of Hong Kong's 10 million
visitors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
