<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Ease on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed in
quiet trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index eased by 2.54 points to close at 2196.81
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 100.49 million units, worth
301.57 million Singapore dollars (about 215.41 million U.S.
dollars). Advances outnumbered declines 159 to 133, while 303
other counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
Ber Group was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 15.13 million units. It was followed by the National
Steel which had 4.36 million shares traded. The Singapore Telecom
was next with 3.19 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign topped the gainers'
list as it gained one dollar to finish at 27.1 Singapore dollars.
The United Overseas Banking (UOB) Foreign rose by 30 cents to 15.5
Singapore dollars, while the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS)
Foreign and the SPH each picked up 20 cents to close at 18.4 and
13 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) was the biggest
loser of the day as it declined by 50 cents to end at 16.5
Singapore dollars. Bukit Sembawang and the City Development fell
by 40 cents each to finish at 31.1 and 12 Singapore dollars
respectively. The Singapore Land was 25 cents lower at 7.75
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
