<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Open Embassy in Guinea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is preparing
for opening an embassy in Conakry to further enhance relations
with Guinea, Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said today.
</P>
<P>
The move to open the embassy was approved by the Cabinet
recently and this has been conveyed to Guinean President Lansana
Conte through its Natural Resources and Energy Minister Fassine
Fofana who is visiting here, he told reporters after meeting
Fofana at the foreign ministry.
</P>
<P>
"The embassy will be opened soon and we are identifying the
candidate to be appointed as ambassador to that country," he said.
</P>
<P>
Guinea, a former French colony in Africa, set up its embassy
here recently and it will be opened by Fofana tonight.
</P>
<P>
On his meeting with Fofana, Abdullah said that they discussed,
among other things, the follow-up of projects jointly planned
during Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad's visit to Guinea
last month.
</P>
<P>
The projects to be undertaken are in the fields of power
generation and telecommunications and in the manufacturing
industry. 
</P>
