<HEADLINE> Macao Inflation Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Macao's inflation rate between
January and October this year dropped to 4.9 percent, according to
the latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that the composite consumer price index (CCPI) grew by 4.9
percent in the first 10 months of the year, compared with 8.6
percent at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same month last year, the CCPI rose by 4
percent in October.
</P>
<P>
The price rise was mainly for such items as garments and
footwear, transportation, fuel and electricity, among others.
</P>
</TEXT>
