<HEADLINE> Congress on Literature, Art Concludes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth National Congress of
the China Federation of Literary and Art Circles (CFLAC) concluded
today in Beijing, with former acting Minister of Culture Zhou
Weizhi elected new chairman of the federation.
</P>
<P>
"Deputies of literary and art circles nationwide have gathered
in China's capital to hold a grand meeting of inheriting the past,
and ushering in the future at a crucial time at the turn of the
century, when the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) decided to promote ethical and cultural progress,"
Zhou, also a well-known composer, said at the closing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Having heard the important speech delivered by Party General
Secretary Jiang Zemin during the meeting, the broad mass of
writers and artists were deeply impressed, and are well aware of
their tasks and responsibilities, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
Zhou stressed that literature and art is a cause of the
Party and the people, and a cause full of vitality.
</P>
<P>
He urged all writers and artists to work hard to invigorate and
promote the development of China's literature and arts, under the
leadership by the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at its
core, and guided by Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,300 people from literary and art circles attended
the five-day meeting. Twenty-two outstanding writers and artists,
including Tibetan singer Cedain Zhoima, were elected new CFLAC
vice-chairmen.  
</P>
</TEXT>
