<HEADLINE> HK Provisional Legislature to be Elected in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Selection Committee for
choosing the first government of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) is scheduled to hold its Fourth
Plenary Session in Shenzhen tomorrow (Saturday).
</P>
<P>
The Committee members will elect 60 members of the Provisional
Legislative Council by secret ballot.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen, chairman of the Preparatory Committee of the Hong
Kong SAR, left Beijing for Shenzhen this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to stipulations on methods for selecting the
Provisional Legislative Council adopted by the Preparatory
Committee, the members of the provisional legislature are selected
by election after the nomination of the candidates by the
Selection Committee.
</P>
<P>
Those candidates should be at least not less than 18 years of
age. They must be permanent Hong Kong residents, support the Basic
Law and pledge to be loyal to the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region.
</P>
<P>
During the session the Selection Committee, composed of 400
permanent Hong Kong residents, will elect 60 legislature members
by secret ballot from 130 candidates who are accorded with the
requirements of the Provisional Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
According to the stipulations, among the elected Provisional
Legislative Council members, the number of those who are of
non-Chinese nationality and have the right of abode in foreign
countries can not surpass 12. 
</P>
