<HEADLINE> 50 Ugandans Die in Capativity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Over 50 people abducted by the
then Zaire-based Allied Democratic Movement Army (ADMA) rebels have
been killed, a report from western Uganda said today.
</P>
<P>
Pauline Katungu, an old woman who escaped from the rebel
captivity, told ''the New Vision'' in Kasese District that the
massacre took place at Kamirongo in Zaire, three kilometers from
the Ugandan border. The tearful woman said she witnessed the
onslaughter on November 17, in which her husband was killed.
</P>
<P>
Intelligence sources said most of the government
officials abducted by the ADMA rebels since mid-November are feared
dead. Among them were six policemen and a customs officer. enditem

