<HEADLINE> China "Sternly Condemns" Hostage-Taking in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- China today sternly condemned
Peru's anti-government organization, Tupac Amaru Revolutionary
Movement, for its holding of hostages in Lima, a Chinese Foreign
Ministry spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang made the statement when
asked whether the Chinese side condemns Peru's anti-government
organization, Tupac Amaru Revolutionary Movement, for its holding
of Peruvian foreign minister and some foreign diplomatic envoys as
hostages.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government expresses "grave concern" over the
incident in which some foreign diplomatic envoys and senior
Peruvian officials, have been held hostage.
</P>
<P>
"We sternly condemn this act of terrorism," he said.
</P>
<P>
China hopes the parties concerned will ensure the safety of the
hostages and find an appropriate solution to the incident as soon
as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
