<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Products Occupy More Domestic Market Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Famous brand-name products
from Shanghai's light industry have maintained a stable growth in
their share of the domestic market, with some holding onto leading
positions.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey conducted on 74 products by the Shanghai
Light Industry Group, ten of the products, such as the "Hero" pen,
"Red Heart" iron, and "Fenghua" ball pen, occupy over half of the
sales in domestic markets.
</P>
<P>
The assessment made by the National Light Industry Council on
eight trades, including bicycles and household appliances, shows
that of the ten consumer concerned products, the Phoenix Bicycle
Factory comes out first among the 12 bicycle factories with annual
sales revenue of 300 million yuan (about 36.1 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Other products like washing machines, refrigerators, and
cosmetics, are also holding leading positions.
</P>
<P>
The increased market coverage is attributed to the introduction
of advanced technology and technology reform.
</P>
<P>
During 1996, Shanghai developed more than 10,000 light industry
products, with a renewal rate of 32 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
