<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabian Company Designates Sales Agent for Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- One of the largest lubricant
producers in the world, based in the Middle East, has designated
the China Shenzhen Pengjunda Industry Investment Company as its
general sales agent for the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi Arabia Petromin Lubricating Oil Company (Petrolube)
and the Shenzen based company today signed an agreement in Beijing
to establish the agency, signifying that China and Saudi Arabia
has made a breakthrough in economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Petromin, attested by API, ISO9002 and BSI, is the trademark of
more than 130 lubricant products of Petrolube. The Petromin
lubricants have found markets in over 30 countries and regions all
over the world.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the introduction of Petromin products will help
ease China's urgent need for quality lubricants for industrial
development.
</P>
<P>
According to an official source, China's production capacity of
lubricated oil stand at some 350,000 tons annually, but the
country suffers from a shortage of quality lubricants. Every year
the country imports more than 300,000 tons of high-grade
lubricants.
</P>
<P>
Petrolube is the largest company under the the world's
leading oil giant Saudi Aramco.
</P>
<P>
Barry Cotton, a senior consultant with the Saudi Aramco, said
that Saudi Arabia and China have a huge potential for cooperation
in oil trade and petrochemical technology, since both countries
are major oil and petrochemical producers in the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
