<HEADLINE> COMESA to Cooperate with UN in Solution of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) will cooperate with the United Nations in
finding solutions to common African problems.
</P>
<P>
The commitment was made by COMESA Secretary General Bingu
Mutharika in his congratulatory message to the in-coming UN
Secretary General, Kofi Annan, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The local press today quoted Mutharika as saying in his message,
''COMESA pledges to cooperate with you and the UN in finding
lasting solutions for Africa.''
</P>
<P>
He noted that as part of the process of globalization, COMESA
believes that African countries should consolidate their markets
through regional economic integration.
</P>
<P>
Mutharika hoped that Kofi Annan would accommodate high priority to
regional economic cooperation and integration in Africa in his new
policy.
</P>
<P>
The COMESA Secretariate is based in Lusaka. enditem

