<HEADLINE> Demand for Zambian Cut Flowers Rises in Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Demand for Zambian cut flowers has
risen in Britain and orders are beyong Zambia's capacity, Zambia
Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
The local newspaper quoted the export review published by the
Export Board of Zambia (EBZ) and the Zambia Export Growers
Association (ZEGA) as saying a total of 41 inquiries were received
during the international flower trade exposition (IFTEX) held in
London recently and the demand is likely to outstrip the supply
capacity of the Zambian exporters.
</P>
<P>
The orders once confirmed will keep the Zambian exporters in
active business for the next two years, according the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
A research made by the EBZ early this year indicated that
Zambia has the capacity to expand its export of cut flowers,
fruits and vegetables by selling directly to the consumers and not
only through the auction system. enditem

