<HEADLINE> More Private Investors in Shanghai Property Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The proportion of private
investment on Shanghai's real estate market is gradually
increasing, "China Land News" has reported.
</P>
<P>
Contrary to the decrease of developers in the property market
in other parts of China, property development enterprises in
Shanghai rose from 2,400 in September of 1995 to 3,000 in this
September. Among the newly opened enterprises, most have received
their investments from private individuals.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based newspaper attributed the pouring of private
capital into the property market to a number of reasons.
</P>
<P>
-- Shanghai municipal government's implementation this year of
a series of policies to enliven the secondary real estate market,
with the policies already proving effective.
</P>
<P>
-- Control of the amount of land supply in the city has been
effective.
</P>
<P>
-- Housing sales volumes in the real estate market continue to
rise, with more and more houses sold.
</P>
<P>
-- Property development remaining attractive, but with funding
for such development tight due to governmental control.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that increase of private capital has diversified
the channels of investment in the real estate sector. It has given
an encouraging sign that the property market has become warmer,
and has also reflected investors' confidence in the market.
</P>
</TEXT>
