<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Opens First T.V. Center Outside Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has opened its first
full-fledged television center outside the capital Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
The 15.6 million US dollar T.V. center was formally opened on
Thursday by Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina at the Pahartali hilltop,
adjacent to the picturesque Foy's lake in the country's largest
port city of Chittagong.
</P>
<P>
The long-awaited T.V. center was constructed under the
financial and technical assistance from the French government. It
will cover a transmission area of 80 km.
</P>
<P>
Reaffirming the government's commitment to the "unfettered
freedom of information," Hasina stressed the importance of
electronic media in the present day world and hoped that "the mass
media will contribute towards the economic progress of the people
and help flourish the nation's culture and heritage."  
</P>
</TEXT>
