<BODY>
<HEADLINE> External Trade Growing in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The amount of overseas
investment flowing to south China's Guangdong Province in the
first 11 months of this year came to 11.7 billion US dollars,
eight percent up from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment took up 40 percent of the total input in
Guangdong's economic development this year, said a local trade
official.
</P>
<P>
This was the third consecutive year that overseas funds to
Guangzhou exceeded 10 billion US dollars, which came from 70
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province exported 4.6 percent more commodities
this year compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Readjustment of export structure boosted export of high-tech
and value-added products. The export volume of computers has
surpassed two billion US dollars so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The province has approved 30,000 foreign-funded enterprises
which are expected to pay 18 billion yuan in taxes this year, 30
percent of Guangdong's total tax income.
nnnn
</P>
