<HEADLINE> Date for 2000 Paralympics Changed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Organizers announced in
Sydney on Friday to change the date of the 2000 Paralympic Games
to make the event run more effeciently.
</P>
<P>
The Paralympic Games will be held from October 18 to 29, four
days after the original schedule.
</P>
<P>
Lois Appleby, chief executive of the Sydney Paralympic
Organizing Committee, announced that the change of date came after
evaluation of the 1996 Atlanta Paralympics.
</P>
<P>
Appleby said the transition period between the 1996 Olympic and
Paralympic Games was totally inadequate and that seriously
impacted on the running of the Paralympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The change of the opening date of the Paralympics will give
additional time to the organizers to get everything ready for the
Paralympics.
</P>
<P>
The 2000 Sydney Olympic Games are scheduled from September 15
to October 1. 
