<HEADLINE> Revolts Spread to More Jails in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi authorities have
put jail guards on red alert as the Jessore central jail in the
Southwest remained besieged for the 5th day today, spilling over
further revolts into Barisal in the South and Tangail in the North
on prisons.
</P>
<P>
Prisoners demanding improved diet and a better living have
seized the control of the Jessore central jail since Monday,
turning down repeated requests from various quarters.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here this morning said that while the rowdy
prisoners of the Jessore central jail are preparing themselves for
a confrontation making lethal weapons inside the jail, pushing the
security forces towards action, at least 100 prisoners and 30
security personnel were injured in Barisal jail during a police
operation inside the prison Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Law-enforcing agencies have reestablished their control in the
Barisal district jail after two hours of the revolt, according to
official sources.
</P>
<P>
In Tangail, the detainees also seized control of the district
jail Thursday, driving out the wardens and holding four jail
officials as hostages.
</P>
<P>
Security personnel of all the central and district jails were
asked to remain on the highest alert to avert any further trouble
in the prisons, the official sources disclosed, adding that Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina has asked the Home Ministry to control the
jail revolts in peaceful ways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
