Krincingwesi aircraft was designed to carry 68 passengers, a few
more than the first N-250 prototype which can carry 50 passengers.
</P>
<P>
IPTN aimed to win 15 percent of the world market for that
aircraft class, he said.
</P>
<P>
"A study revealed that between 4,000 and 6,000 aircraft of the
N-250 class would be needed in the next two decades," he said.
</P>
<P>
IPTN has received orders for about 200 N-250s which cost
between 13.5 million and 14.2 million US dollars each, he
disclosed.  
