<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen, one of the country's
five special economic zones, recently set up a school for foreign
children living in the city.
</P>
<P>
Located in east China's Fujian Province, the city now has 4,000
foreign-funded enterprises and a number of overseas investors
looking for an English-based school curriculum for their children.
</P>
