<HEADLINE> Eastern Province Leads China in Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 20 (Xinhua)-- Urban residents in China's
Zhejiang Province now have 10.9 square meters of living space per
person, three sq m greater than the country's average, and putting
it first among all provinces.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's housing construction is characterized by
well-planned residential districts that serve as examples. More
than 620,000 households moved into new housing in the past five
years thanks to local government efforts at helping out families
who were living in less than four sq.m. of space per capita.
</P>
<P>
Over 25 million square meters of old housing was leveled to
make room for 99 million sq m of new housing during that period.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has added housing construction
subsidies to its budget to help those who can't solve the housing
problem by themselves alone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
