<HEADLINE> South China City to Establish Health Files for Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Haikou, capital city of south
China's Hainan Province, will carry out a health census among
local residents, based on which, charge-free computerized health
files will be established for its citizens.
</P>
<P>
The census will include two parts, a survey on health
conditions of local residents and a competition of common people
on health questions. All the information will be filed into
computers by January, 1997.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the first group of health promotion
activists will be selected according to the answers given by local
residents in the competition.
</P>
<P>
To establish health files is an important measure Haikou city
government will take to implement the health project. The project
is the first of the ten projects Haikou will implement for the
building of a health city.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Health selected Haikou as a pilot city
to implement the health city plan in 1995.  
</P>
