<HEADLINE> East China's High-tech Sector Developing Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 20 (Xinhua)-- The amount of added value in
the high-tech industry in Zhejiang Province is expected to account
for 20 percent of the total added value for all industry by the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
This will be an increase of seven percentage points from
today's figure, a provincial official said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, more than 410 companies have moved to
high-tech development zones in Hangzhou, the provincial capital,
230 of which are defined as high-tech enterprises. More than 102
businesses outside the province's zones are also defined as
high-tech ones.
</P>
<P>
Sales of high-tech products totaled 57.1 billion yuan in the
past five years, with an average annual increase of 36 percent.
</P>
<P>
A "New Century Program" is being put into operation in an
effort to further develop the province's high-tech industries.
</P>
