<HEADLINE> East China Province Becoming Popular Tourism Hot Spots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province in east
China has received 36 million domestic tourists since the
beginning of this year and has earned 22 billion yuan from tourism
services.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, tourism earnings now account for
6.4 percent of this province's gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang, with many beautiful scenic sites, has great
potentials for tourism development. The provincial tourism
administration has worked out 10 measures to promote the
development of domestic tourism, which has given impetus to the
emergence of many new tourism programs.
</P>
<P>
The province has been blessed with 130 new scenic spots, 300
new hotels and restaurants, an increase of 80,000 beds, and 281
new travel agencies.
</P>
<P>
