<HEADLINE> Celebrations to Mark Victory of Long March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- Yan'an, a city in northern
Shaanxi Province which was once the center of the Chinese
revolution, will hold a series of celebrations to mark the 60th
anniversary of the the city as the headquarters of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC) and senior Chinese
leaders.
</P>
<P>
The red army moved into the city at the end of the long march
some 60 years ago, and Yan'an has since been kown to the world.
</P>
<P>
To mark the event, the local government has renovated a group
of former revolutionary sites and the Yan'an Revolutionary
Memorial Hall.
</P>
<P>
A bronze statue of the late leader Mao Zedong has been built
and will be unveiled on January 13 -- the anniversary of the date
when the CPC Central Committee and senior Chinese leaders marched
into the city.
</P>
<P>
Other activities will include commemorative meetings, lectures
on Yan'an's development and construction, exhibitions of paintings
and photos on Yan'an's great achievements in the past decades, and
artistic performances. 
</P>
