<HEADLINE> Shanghai Installs Exhaust Purifiers on Motor Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 80,000 motor
vehicles in Shanghai, China's largest manufacturing and commercial
center, have been installed with exhaust purifiers.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government plans to install purifiers on 100,000
motor vehicles this year, as a research conclusion from Shanghai
Medical Sciences University shows that motor vehicle exhausts may
cause cancer, the "China Communications" reports.
</P>
<P>
The traffic police headquarters of Shanghai has announced that
vehicles which are found to have no purifiers will see the
drivers' licences revoked for a month. 
</P>
