<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Preparing for '97 Tourism Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The Visit China '97 Program is
expected to bring the number of overseas and domestic tourists to
northwest China's Shaanxi Province to 530,000 and 25 million,
respectively, acccording to local tourism organizers here today.
</P>
<P>
Overseas tourism will earn the province 210 million US dollars
in 1997, a 10.5 percent rise over this year, and revenues from
domestic tourism will reach 6.7 billion yuan, compared with 6.1
billion yuan anticipated for 1996, they say.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goal, the provincial tourism bureau will further
tap new markets in southeast Asia, the Republic of Korea, northern
Europe, and Australia. Currently, about 80 percent of Shaanxi's
foreign tourists are from Japan, northern America, and western
Europe.
</P>
<P>
As part of the efforts to expand tourist markets, the ancient
city of Xi'an will cooperate with Beijing, Shanghai, and Guilin,
three other hot Chinese tourist cities, to push the program.
</P>
<P>
And Shaanxi is projected to organize more overseas tourists to
the ancient Silk Road, together with other provinces in northwest
China.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province will present tourists a series of
activities featuring the Qin culture (221-207 B.C), as well as
local natural scenery and folklore.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
