<HEADLINE> China to Spread the Use of Pollution-Free Pesticides </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, December 20 (Xinhua) -- China is set to spread
the use of pollution-free pesticides made from herbs in the coming
years.
</P>
<P>
Development of the pesticides was listed by the State Science
and Technology Commission as one of the state major high-tech and
new technology development projects in the Ninth Five-Year Plan
period (1996 to 2000).
</P>
<P>
The effective and safe pesticides were developed by the
Shijiazhuang Institute of Plant Pesticides with advanced
techniques, and they have passed official appraisal and are
patented.
</P>
<P>
Researchers of the institutes chose sophora favescens ait,
brucea javanica and some other traditional Chinese herbs as the
raw materials and made the herbal pesticides that can kill insects
and stimulate crop growth as well.
</P>
<P>
As the herbal pesticides do not contain any chemical
composition, it can be easily desolved in the air and soil without
any ecological pollution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
