<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All Rural Villages in Tangshan Have Access to Highways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 20 (Xinhua) -- The city of Tangshan, which
was almost leveled in the 1976 earthquake, in north China's Hebei
Province, reports that every village on its outskirts now has
access to highways.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this, the city invested a total of 81.5 million yuan
to build rural highways this year, and of the funds, 64.5 million
yuan was provided by local counties, townships, and villages.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the city still had 106 villages with
no access to highways. All townships in Tangshan were linked up
with asphalt-paved highways in 1995. So far, the more than 500
villages all have access to highways. This facilitates the
development of the rural economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
