<HEADLINE> Italian Investments in Argentina Grow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 19 (Xinhua) -- Italian investments in
Argentina from 1994 to the present have amounted to 2.5 billion
U.S. dollars, according to a recent report by the private
foundation, Invertir.
</P>
<P>
The amount would hit 3.45 billion dollars by 1998, and that
would not include investments by Italian entrepreneurs in
privatizations, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The investments are channeled to many sectors including
telecommunications, food industries, electric home appliances,
motor vehicles and automotive parts, and gas transportation.
</P>
<P>
The Stet company is planning to invest two billion dollars to
expand and digitalize telephone lines in Argentina, the most
important project in telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The Fiat motor company foresees a 600-million dollar investment
which will start on Friday with the first stage construction of
its plant in the central Cordoba province. 
</P>
