<HEADLINE> 10 Bangladeshis Killed in Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 persons were killed
and 30 others injured Thursday when a passenger bus fell into a
200-yard deep roadside ditch at Kalapania near Feni, a district in
southeast Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here late last night, the
accident occurred when the driver lost control over the steering
and the bus carrying 45 passengers skidded off and fell into about
200 yards deep ditch.
</P>
<P>
The 10 persons died on the spot, local police said, adding that
among the injured, seven persons were in critical conditions.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the bus remained untraced.
</P>
<P>
In her condolence Thursday, Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina expressed her profound grief and sorrow at the death of the
10 persons in the tragic accident.  
</P>
