<DATE_TIME> 1996-12-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Shoot Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 19 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks shot higher
today, led by consumer and financial issues, with the Dow Jones
industrial average jumping 126.87 points to 6,473.64, a gain of 2
percent.
</P>
<P>
That was the best one-day gain in the blue-chip index since it
rose 110.55 last March 11. But the Dow is still 73 points below
its record high of 6,547.79 set on November 25.
</P>
<P>
The market was led by consumer and financial issues, as bond
prices were driven sharply higher on weak economic data and strong
demand for a Treasury auction of 5-year notes.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by 7 to 3 on the New
York Stock Exchange. Volume was heavy at 522.32 million shares, up
from Wednesday's pace.
</P>
<P>
Broad stock indexes were also sharply higher.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock index rose 14.23 to 745.77, and
the NYSE's composite index rose 6.99 to 392.16.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 10.49 to 1,295.87, and the
American Stock Exchange's market added 3.57 to 578.53.
</P>
<P>
Stocks rose with bonds after the government revised
unemployment claims sharply upward and said the nation's trade
deficit had narrowed by 30 percent in October.
</P>
<P>
The market was also encouraged by a report from the
Philadelphia Federal Reserve showing a sharp decline in the area's
general business activity in December.
</P>
<P>
In the afternoon, news of very strong demand for the Treasury
auction helped doubled the Dow's already strong daily gains. The
Treasury sold 12.50 billion U.S. dollars of five-year notes at
6.165 percent, up from 5.95 percent in November.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year Treasury bond's yielding was down to 6.59 percent
from 6.65 percent on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Consumer stocks, such as health care, food and beverages and
household products, all rose, as well as financial stocks as
interest rates declined.
</P>
<P>
Major gainers in Nasdaq trading were Intel, Microsoft, Cisco
Systems and Dell Computer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
