<HEADLINE> Border Opens between Hungary, Croatian E. Slavonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, December 19 (Xinhua) - the Croatian and Hungarian
governments as well as a UN administrative body on Thursday signed
an agreement on the opening of a border-crossing between Hungary
and Croatia's Eastern Slavonia.
</P>
<P>
Border crossing between Hungary and Eastern Slavonia has been
closed since the region was taken over by Croatian Serbs in 1991.
Under an agreement signed last December, Eastern Slavonia will
return to Croatia after a maximum two year transition period under
the UN administration.
</P>
<P>
The agreement on Thursday said that the Knezevo-Udvar crossing,
to be opened from January 1997, will allow civilian transport by
vehicles with Croatian plates through the U.N.-administered area
for the first time in five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
