<HEADLINE> IDB Approves $85 Mln for Argentine Water Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 19 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of 85 million
U.S. dollar in financing to support the investment plan of an
Argentine water and sewerage company.
</P>
<P>
It is the first financing by IDB's private sector department
for a water and sanitation project, and also the first IDB
financing for an Argentine utility company outside of the Buenos
Aires metropolitan area.
</P>
<P>
The IDB resources will help Aguas Provinciales de Santa Fe S.A.
finance the rehabilitation and expansion of water treatment and
sewerage facilities, improving the overall quality of the
services.
</P>
<P>
The financing consists of a 30 million dollar loan from the
IDB's ordinary capital, and a second loan of 55 million dollars
from syndicated funds provided by commercial banks through
participation agreements with the IDB.
</P>
<P>
The Argentina company provides services to an area that
includes 60 percent of the province's population. The company
supplies potable water to some 1.5 million people and offers
sewerage services to 750,000 customers.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the IDB's Multilateral Investment Fund (MIF), an
autonomous fund administered by the IDB, approved a 3 million
dollar grant for small rural producers in Argentina to help
improve the business management skills and competitiveness.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
