<HEADLINE> Kenya's New Police Commissioner Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 19 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi today appointed Dancan Kabethi Wachira the Commissioner of
Police to replace Shadrack Kiruki with immediate effect.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, 15 police officers were detained following the
killing of two students at Nairobi's Kenyatta University, Senior
Superintendent Peter Kimanthi said today.
</P>
<P>
The two students were shot dead by police during a protest
against the killing of a student by the police at Egerton
University on Tuesday near Nakuru, about 150 kilometers northwest
of Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
A government statement issued on Wednesday said that actions
will be taken against those responsible for these incidents.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan police had been firmly instructed to use only rubber
bullets to disperse students following the death of the student
at Egerton University on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Investigations are being carried out to determine why the
instructions which were given only a day earlier were defied so
soon, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The two universities have been closed after the killings.
</P>
</TEXT>
