<HEADLINE> Londoners Urged to Keep Alert on IRA Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 19 (Xinhua) -- The Irish Republican Army (IRA)
could be planning pre-Christmas attacks on shopping centers in the
British capital and people should keep an eye out for any
suspicious activity, London's chief of police warned today.
</P>
<P>
Metropolitan Police Commissioner Paul Condon said the IRA had a
history of launching attacks against shoppers crowding into the
city before Christmas, seeing it as a prime time to publicize
their cause.
</P>
<P>
Condon said his force was on alert for assassinations, bomb
attacks and fire-bombings, urging people in London to be on their
guard.
</P>
<P>
According to BBC Television, anti-terrorist police have
appealed for information about a Ford Iveco lorry that may have
used by the IRA to transport bomb-making equipment.
</P>
<P>
It is believed the vehicle may have been used to take material
from Northern Ireland to the mainland.
</P>
<P>
The IRA abandoned a 17-month cease-fire in February and
detonated a huge device in eastern London in the first of a series
of bombings on the mainland to press its campaign for a united
Ireland.  
</P>
</TEXT>
