<HEADLINE> EU Condemns Hostage-Taking Incident in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
condemned the hostage-taking incident in Peru with several hundred
people including some senior diplomats being held captive,
according to press reports from Dublin.
</P>
<P>
The current EU president Ireland issued a statement earlier
today on behalf of the 15-nation bloc, urging the hostage takers
to release all the hostages immediately by international law.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed that the EU felt sure that the Peruvian
government would do everything to protect the lives of the
hostages.
</P>
<P>
In other developments, the British government has decided to
send a group of experts to Lima, Peru to help resolve the hostage
crisis.
</P>
<P>
It was reported heavily-armed local guerillas stormed the
Japanese embassy in Lima on Tuesday and demanded the release of
their jailed comrades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
